pav:providedBy  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4858  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"We found that cLTP increased the surface GluA1 level in putative inhibitory interneurons; these changes were prevented by knocking down γCaMKII with shRNA (Fig. 5).\n\nTo investigate this process further, we monitored the phosphorylation of the AMPAR subunit GluA1 at Ser831 (pGluA1), the key step downstream of CaMKII activation during LTPE→E induction in excitatory neurons [2, 3]. We found that the γCaMKII shRNA, but not its scrambled control, inhibited cLTP-induced changes in pGluA1 (Fig. 6).\n\nFinally, the necessity of γCaMKII in the cLTP of inhibitory interneurons was probed by an shRNA-resistant construct (γCaMKIIR). With endogenous γCaMKII knocked down, 'wild-type' γCaMKIIR fully rescued pGluA1 and the surface GluA1 level (Figs. 5, 6). In contrast, γCaMKIIR K43R (the kinase-dead form [20]) was unable to rescue them (Figs. 5, 6), indicating that the kinase activity of γCaMKII is required to regulate AMPARs during cLTP of inhibitory interneurons.\". Experimental description: MYM: \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from Sprague-Dawley rat pups at postnatal days 0-1.\"\n\nantibody / target sequence:\nrabbit anti-γCaMKII antibody (1:500, ab01)\n\nrat γCaMKII shRNA sequence (5'-TGGCCTGGCCATCGAAGTGCA-3') was subcloned into the pLVTHM vector (12247, Addgene, Watertown, USA) following the manufacturers' protocol." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4858" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

